-- Indian Sitarist Ravi Shankar Dies at 92, Manager Says
-- B y   S i d d h a r t h   P h i l i p
-- 2012-12-12T04:03:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-12/indian-sitarist-ravi-shankar-dies-at-92-manager-blackburn-says.html
Ravi Shankar, the sitarist and
composer described as the “godfather of world music” by Beatles
guitarist  George Harrison , has died. He was 92.  “It’s with a very heavy heart that I confirm this sad
news,” his manager Earl Blackburn, said in an e-mail today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
